We should also check if the client data actually loads when the JS runs. We could curl the API endpoint directly to make sure the tRPC API works.

`curl http://localhost:3000/api/trpc/hello?input={"name":"Client"}` — but the exact URL for a batched tRPC query might be different. In tRPC v11 with the fetch adapter and httpBatchLink, the client makes POST requests to `/api/trpc`. For a single query, the client might send a POST request with JSON body containing a batch. We can test with `curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/trpc -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"0":{"json":{"name":"Client"}}

